  "verdict": "The diagnostic refutes an excess response-poll/wakeup-churn hypothesis. Every scenario averages exactly two response-head read polls and one pending per request; HTTPS-origin scenarios show two TLS-read pendings per request because proxy TLS and origin TLS are both active. The remaining gap is therefore the unavoidable sequential request-response wait boundary or deeper runtime I/O scheduling cost, not a repeated-poll loop that can be eliminated locally."
